” website package</strong> for you — pages, admin dashboard, contact form, gallery placeholders, and a reviews page.</p>
<p data-start="181" data-end="263"><strong data-start="181" data-end="202">Download it here:</strong> <span class="" data-state="closed"><button class="behavior-btn hover:entity-accent focus-visible:focus-ring entity-underline inline cursor-pointer appearance-none border-0 bg-transparent p-0 text-start align-baseline text-inherit" type="button">bevsrepair_site.zip</button></span></p>
<h3 data-start="265" data-end="282">What’s inside</h3>
<ul data-start="283" data-end="669">
<li data-start="283" data-end="355">
<p data-start="285" data-end="355"><strong data-start="285" data-end="334">Home / Services / Gallery / Reviews / Contact</strong> (+ a thank-you page)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="356" data-end="435">
<p data-start="358" data-end="435"><strong data-start="358" data-end="368">/admin</strong> editor (Decap CMS) so you can update content/photos without coding</p>
</li>
<li data-start="436" data-end="505">
<p data-start="438" data-end="505"><strong data-start="438" data-end="454">Netlify form</strong> on the Contact page (works once hosted on Netlify)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="506" data-end="558">
<p data-start="508" data-end="558">Placeholder gallery images you can replace anytime</p>
</li>
<li data-start="559" data-end="669">
<p data-start="561" data-end="669">Reviews added in a clean format (based on what I could access online). <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center select-none relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill" style="width: 90px;"><a href="https://reviews.birdeye.com/bevs-repair-167530603544188" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://reviews.birdeye.com/bevs-repair-167530603544188" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!" style="max-width: 90px;"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between overflow-hidden" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Birdeye Experience Marketing platform</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="671" data-end="709">One important note about your logo</h3>
<p data-start="710" data-end="904">I <strong data-start="712" data-end="783">couldn’t automatically embed the logo image you posted into the ZIP</strong> from here (it didn’t come through as a downloadable file on my side), so the site currently uses a <strong data-start="883" data-end="903">logo placeholder</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="906" data-end="916">To fix it:</p>
<ol data-start="917" data-end="1085">
<li data-start="917" data-end="958">
<p data-start="920" data-end="958">Save your logo as <strong data-start="938" data-end="945">PNG</strong> or <strong data-start="949" data-end="956">SVG</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="959" data-end="991">
<p data-start="962" data-end="991">Drop it into: <code data-start="976" data-end="989">assets/img/</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="992" data-end="1085">
<p data-start="995" data-end="1085">Replace <code data-start="1003" data-end="1025">logo-placeholder.svg</code> references in the HTML with your file name (ex: <code data-start="1074" data-end="1084">logo.png</code>)</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="1087" data-end="1213">If you upload the logo again as an actual <strong data-start="1129" data-end="1144">file upload</strong> (PNG/SVG), I’ll plug it into the site and update every page for you.</p>

