<p data-start="70" data-end="129">The message from <strong data-start="87" data-end="128"><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Netlify</span></span></strong>:</p>
<blockquote data-start="131" data-end="191">
<p data-start="133" data-end="191"><strong data-start="133" data-end="191">“bevsrepair.ca doesn’t appear to be served by Netlify”</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="193" data-end="217">means one of two things:</p>
<p data-start="219" data-end="350">1️⃣ DNS hasn’t <strong data-start="234" data-end="258">fully propagated yet</strong><br data-start="258" data-end="261">
2️⃣ One of the DNS records is still pointing to <strong data-start="309" data-end="350"><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Webador</span></span></strong></p>
<p data-start="352" data-end="416">The good news: this is <strong data-start="375" data-end="415">very normal right after changing DNS</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="418" data-end="421">
<h1 data-start="423" data-end="462">First thing to try (very often works)</h1>
<p data-start="463" data-end="469">Click:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="471" data-end="501"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-ni7q5mnh.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>Retry DNS verification</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="503" data-end="529">Then wait <strong data-start="513" data-end="528">2–3 minutes</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="531" data-end="580">Sometimes Netlify just needs to re-check the DNS.</p>
<hr data-start="582" data-end="585">
<h1 data-start="587" data-end="610">Second thing to check</h1>
<p data-start="611" data-end="666">Make sure these <strong data-start="627" data-end="665">exact records exist in Webador DNS</strong>:</p>
