<hr data-start="1192" data-end="1195">
<h1 data-start="1197" data-end="1216">Why this happened</h1>
<p data-start="1217" data-end="1328">Webador allows blank host records, but <strong data-start="1256" data-end="1327">Netlify’s verification expects the root domain to be explicitly <code data-start="1322" data-end="1325">@</code></strong>.</p>
<p data-start="1330" data-end="1403">The site works already — Netlify just couldn’t confirm ownership for SSL.</p>
<hr data-start="1405" data-end="1408">
