<p data-start="39" data-end="168">Let’s use today to make the site feel <em data-start="77" data-end="83">real</em> (photos + estimate form + polish). Here’s the quickest path with the biggest payoff.</p>
<hr data-start="170" data-end="173">
<h1 data-start="175" data-end="210">1) Turn on Force HTTPS (1 minute)</h1>
<p data-start="211" data-end="252">In Netlify: <strong data-start="223" data-end="252">Domain management → HTTPS</strong></p>
<ul data-start="253" data-end="280">
<li data-start="253" data-end="280">
<p data-start="255" data-end="280">Toggle <strong data-start="262" data-end="277">Force HTTPS</strong> ON</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="282" data-end="328">That guarantees everyone hits the secure site.</p>
<hr data-start="330" data-end="333">
<h1 data-start="335" data-end="382">2) Make the logo bigger + cleaner (5 minutes)</h1>
<p data-start="383" data-end="437">You were already in <code data-start="403" data-end="415">index.html</code> and the logo line is:</p>
