<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="832" data-end="854"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-ni7q5mnh.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>Commit changes</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="856" data-end="931">Then <strong data-start="861" data-end="930"><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Netlify</span></span> will redeploy automatically</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="933" data-end="1016">Refresh your website after about <strong data-start="966" data-end="980">10 seconds</strong> and the logo should be much larger.</p>
<hr data-start="1018" data-end="1021">
<h1 data-start="1023" data-end="1070">One more thing I noticed from your screenshot</h1>
<p data-start="1071" data-end="1134">Your logo image itself might also be <strong data-start="1108" data-end="1133">very small resolution</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="1136" data-end="1182">If it still looks small after this fix, I can:</p>
<ul data-start="1184" data-end="1239">
<li data-start="1184" data-end="1196">
<p data-start="1186" data-end="1196">sharpen it</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1197" data-end="1209">
<p data-start="1199" data-end="1209">enlarge it</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1210" data-end="1239">
<p data-start="1212" data-end="1239">optimize it for the website</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1241" data-end="1273">so it looks crisp in the header.</p>
