c7dfd3fa6" data-testid="conversation-turn-114" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant"><h6 class="sr-only select-none">ChatGPT said:</h6><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div tabindex="-1" class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="f1799c71-a07d-48fe-bdd8-aa6c260f22bf" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2-thinking" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="41">Awesome — that narrows it down perfectly.</p>
<p data-start="43" data-end="210">Since the <strong data-start="53" data-end="74">Netlify URL works</strong> and your deploy is <strong data-start="94" data-end="107">Published</strong>, the site is healthy. The problem is <strong data-start="145" data-end="189">only the custom domain handshake/routing</strong> for <code data-start="194" data-end="209">bevsrepair.ca</code>.</p>
<h3 data-start="212" data-end="244">What’s most likely happening</h3>
<p data-start="245" data-end="262">One of these two:</p>
<ol data-start="263" data-end="546">
<li data-start="263" data-end="418">
<p data-start="266" data-end="418"><strong data-start="266" data-end="367">Netlify “Force HTTPS” isn’t the issue — you’re on the new Netlify UI where the toggle isn’t shown</strong>, and HTTPS is automatic once the cert is issued.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="419" data-end="546">
<p data-start="422" data-end="546"><strong data-start="422" data-end="469">Your browser/ISP is caching a bad SSL route</strong> (very common right after DNS + cert changes), even though the cert is valid.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="548" data-end="595">Let’s fix it with the next best checks/actions.</p>
<hr data-start="597" data-end="600">
<h1 data-start="602" data-end="645">1) Try this exact URL (tests www vs root)</h1>
<p data-start="646" data-end="698">Open in a fresh window after restarting the browser:</p>
<p data-start="700" data-end="731"><strong data-start="700" data-end="731"><code data-start="702" data-end="729">https://www.bevsrepair.ca</code></strong></p>
<ul data-start="733" data-end="876">
<li data-start="733" data-end="809">
<p data-start="735" data-end="809">If <strong data-start="738" data-end="751">www works</strong> but root doesn’t → it’s a root-domain DNS/redirect issue.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="810" data-end="876">
<p data-start="812" data-end="876">If <strong data-start="815" data-end="828">both fail</strong> → it’s cached SSL/HSTS or a DNS resolver issue.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="878" data-end="887">Also try:</p>
<p data-start="889" data-end="948"><strong data-start="889" data-end="915"><code data-start="891" data-end="913">http://bevsrepair.ca</code></strong><br data-start="915" data-end="918">
<strong data-start="918" data-end="948"><code data-start="920" data-end="946">http://www.bevsrepair.ca</code></strong></p>
<p data-start="950" data-end="995">(We’re just testing which endpoint responds.)</p>
<hr data-start="997" data-end="1000">
<h1 data-start="1002" data-end="1067">2) In Netlify: set the primary domain to WWW (quick workaround)</h1>
<p data-start="1068" data-end="1126">This often instantly fixes weird root-domain SSL behavior.</p>
<p data-start="1128" data-end="1192">In Netlify → <strong data-start="1141" data-end="1162">Domain management</strong> (where you see both domains):</p>
<ol data-start="1193" data-end="1276">
<li data-start="1193" data-end="1240">
<p data-start="1196" data-end="1240">Click <strong data-start="1202" data-end="1213">Options</strong> beside <code data-start="1221" data-end="1240">www.bevsrepair.ca</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1241" data-end="1276">
<p data-start="1244" data-end="1276">Choose <strong data-start="1251" data-end="1276">Set as primary domain</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="1278" data-end="1343">Netlify will automatically redirect the other one to the primary.</p>
<p data-start="1345" data-end="1375">After doing that, try loading:</p>
<p data-start="1377" data-end="1415"><strong data-start="1377" data-end="1408"><code data-start="1379" data-end="1406">https://www.bevsrepair.ca</code></strong> first.</p>
<hr data-start="1417" data-end="1420">
<h1 data-start="1422" data-end="1479">3) Confirm Webador DNS matches Netlify’s required setup</h1>
<p data-start="1480" data-end="1567">Even if you don’t see AAAA records, one wrong/extra record can confuse the root domain.</p>
<p data-start="1569" data-end="1605">You want ONLY these for web hosting:</p>
<h3 data-start="1607" data-end="1635">Root domain (blank or @)</h3>
<ul data-start="1636" data-end="1675">
<li data-start="1636" data-end="1653">
<p data-start="1638" data-end="1653">A → <code data-start="1642" data-end="1653">75.2.60.5</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1654" data-end="1675">
<p data-start="1656" data-end="1675">A → <code data-start="1660" data-end="1675">99.83.190.102</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1677" data-end="1684">WWW</h3>
<ul data-start="1685" data-end="1740">
<li data-start="1685" data-end="1740">
<p data-start="1687" data-end="1740">CNAME <code data-start="1693" data-end="1698">www</code> → <code data-start="1701" data-end="1740">sprightly-monstera-5d76d8.netlify.app</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1742" data-end="1761">And <strong data-start="1746" data-end="1760">remove any</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start="1762" data-end="1859">
<li data-start="1762" data-end="1813">
<p data-start="1764" data-end="1813">A record pointing to <code data-start="1785" data-end="1799">35.204.150.5</code> (old Webador)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1814" data-end="1859">
<p data-start="1816" data-end="1859">CNAME <code data-start="1822" data-end="1825">*</code> → <code data-start="1828" data-end="1859">website-rendering.webador.com</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1861" data-end="1891">(Those can break SSL routing.)</p>
<hr data-start="1893" data-end="1896">
<h1 data-start="1898" data-end="1939">4) Try a different network (quick test)</h1>
<p data-start="1940" data-end="1969">If you can, test the site on:</p>
<ul data-start="1970" data-end="2011">
<li data-start="1970" data-end="2011">
<p data-start="1972" data-end="2011">your phone on <strong data-start="1986" data-end="1999">cell data</strong> (not Wi-Fi)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2013" data-end="2134">If it works on cell data but not your Wi-Fi/PC → it’s 100% a DNS/SSL cache with your local network/provider, not Netlify.</p>
<hr data-start="2136" data-end="2139">
<h2 data-start="2141" data-end="2170">Do this now (fastest path)</h2>
<ol data-start="2171" data-end="2311">
<li data-start="2171" data-end="2210">
<p data-start="2174" data-end="2210">Restart Chrome (you’re doing this)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2211" data-end="2247">
<p data-start="2214" data-end="2247">Try <code data-start="2218" data-end="2245">https://www.bevsrepair.ca</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="2248" data-end="2311">
<p data-start="2251" data-end="2311">If it still fails, set <strong data-start="2274" data-end="2299">www as primary domain</strong> in Netlify.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="2313" data-end="2447" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">Reply with what happens on <strong data-start="2340" data-end="2347">www</strong> after your restart (loads / doesn’t load + any error text), and I’ll tell you the exact next click.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex min-h-[46px] justify-start"><div class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none touch:w-[calc(100%+--spacing(3.5))] -mt-1 w-[calc(100%+--spacing(2.5))] duration-[1.5s] focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto pointer-events-none [mask-image:linear-gradient(to_right,black_33%,transparent_66%)] [mask-size:300%_100%] [mask-position:100%_0%] motion-safe:transition-[mask-position] group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:[mask-position:0_0] group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:[mask-position:0_0] has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:[mask-position:0_0]" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy" aria-pressed="false" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-ni7q5mnh.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Good response" aria-pressed="false" data-testid="good-response-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-ni7q5mnh.svg#51753c" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><butt