<h3 data-start="41" data-end="87"><code data-start="45" data-end="56">README.md</code> is <strong data-start="60" data-end="87">not part of the website</strong></h3>
<p data-start="88" data-end="183">It’s just a <strong data-start="100" data-end="137">documentation file for developers</strong> on <strong data-start="141" data-end="182"><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">GitHub</span></span></strong>.</p>
<p data-start="185" data-end="217">It usually contains things like:</p>
<ul data-start="219" data-end="316">
<li data-start="219" data-end="240">
<p data-start="221" data-end="240">What the project is</p>
</li>
<li data-start="241" data-end="264">
<p data-start="243" data-end="264">How the website works</p>
</li>
<li data-start="265" data-end="291">
<p data-start="267" data-end="291">Instructions for editing</p>
</li>
<li data-start="292" data-end="316">
<p data-start="294" data-end="316">Notes about deployment</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="318" data-end="370">Visitors to <strong data-start="330" data-end="347">bevsrepair.ca</strong> will <strong data-start="353" data-end="369">never see it</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="372" data-end="375">
<h3 data-start="377" data-end="413">Example of what it might contain</h3>
<p data-start="414" data-end="429">Something like:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="431" data-end="588"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-ni7q5mnh.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>Bev's Repair Website</span><br><br><span>Static website deployed with Netlify.</span><br><br><span>Pages:</span><br><span>- Home</span><br><span>- Services</span><br><span>- Gallery</span><br><span>- Reviews</span><br><span>- Contact</span><br><br><span>Edit content in /content folder.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="590" data-end="634">It only shows on the GitHub repository page.</p>
<hr data-start="636" data-end="639">
<h3 data-start="641" data-end="670">Do you need to upload it?</h3>
<p data-start="671" data-end="684"><strong data-start="671" data-end="684">Optional.</strong></p>
<p data-start="686" data-end="699">Uploading it:</p>
<ul data-start="700" data-end="770">
<li data-start="700" data-end="728">
<p data-start="702" data-end="728">keeps the repository clean</p>
</li>
<li data-start="729" data-end="770">
<p data-start="731" data-end="770">helps remember how the site works later</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="772" data-end="824">But the site will run <strong data-start="794" data-end="823">perfectly fine without it</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="826" data-end="829">
<h3 data-start="831" data-end="852">My recommendation</h3>
<p data-start="853" data-end="916">Upload <strong data-start="860" data-end="881">everything anyway</strong> just to keep the project complete:</p>
