<p data-start="1205" data-end="1251">And your CSS must target <code data-start="1230" data-end="1240">.bullets</code> like this:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1253" data-end="1414"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-ni7q5mnh.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>CSS</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-ni7q5mnh.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>.</span><span class="ͼl">bullets</span><span> {</span><br><span>  margin-top: </span><span class="ͼj">10</span><span class="ͼg">px</span><span>;</span><br><span>  padding-left: </span><span class="ͼj">18</span><span class="ͼg">px</span><span>;</span><br><span>  columns: </span><span class="ͼj">2</span><span>;</span><br><span>  column-gap: </span><span class="ͼj">60</span><span class="ͼg">px</span><span>;</span><br><span>}</span><br><br><span>.</span><span class="ͼl">bullets</span><span> </span><span class="ͼo">li</span><span> {</span><br><span>  margin-bottom: </span><span class="ͼj">6</span><span class="ͼg">px</span><span>;</span><br><span>  break-inside: </span><span class="ͼj">avoid</span><span>;</span><br><span>}</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="1416" data-end="1494">⚠️ If your <code data-start="1427" data-end="1433">&lt;ul&gt;</code> doesn’t have <code data-start="1447" data-end="1464">class="bullets"</code> exactly, the CSS won’t apply.</p>
<hr data-start="1496" data-end="1499">
<h2 data-start="1501" data-end="1552">Quick check that tells us instantly what’s wrong</h2>
<p data-start="1553" data-end="1657">Open the Services page → right click one of the bullets → <strong data-start="1611" data-end="1622">Inspect</strong> → click the <code data-start="1635" data-end="1657">&lt;ul class="bullets"&gt;</code></p>
<p data-start="1659" data-end="1701">On the right, search for <strong data-start="1684" data-end="1698"><code data-start="1686" data-end="1696">.bullets</code></strong>.</p>
<ul data-start="1702" data-end="1868">
<li data-start="1702" data-end="1795">
<p data-start="1704" data-end="1795">If you <strong data-start="1711" data-end="1727">don’t see it</strong>, the CSS file being loaded isn’t the one you edited (or caching).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1796" data-end="1868">
<p data-start="1798" data-end="1868">If you <strong data-start="1805" data-end="1818">do see it</strong>, but no columns, something else is overriding it.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1870" data-end="1873">
<h3 data-start="1875" data-end="1937">Send me 1 screenshot and I’ll tell you exactly which it is</h3>
